parator\"><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-secondary leading-relaxed italic\">“<!-- -->Slow and repetitive. The husband is insufferable and the wife deserved better writing.<!-- -->”</p></blockquote><div class=\"mt-4\"><p class=\"text-[12px] font-semibold text-text-secondary uppercase tracking-wider mb-2\">Where to watch</p><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-primary\"><span class=\"text-accent font-medium\">Free: </span>Tubi, Plex, Roku Channel</p><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-primary mt-1\"><span class=\"text-text-secondary\">Rent/Buy: </span>Apple TV, Amazon Video, Fandango At Home</p></div><div class=\"mt-5 flex items-center gap-4\"><button class=\"flex items-center gap-1.5 py-1 transition-opacity hover:opacity-70\" aria-label=\"Save\"><svg width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#6E6E73\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\"><path d=\"M5 4a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h10a2 2 0 0 1 2 2v18l-7-4-7 4V4z\"></path></svg><span class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary\">Save for later</span></button><button class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary hover:text-text-primary transition-colors py-1\">Already seen</button><button class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary hover:text-text-primary transition-colors py-1\">Not for me</button></div></div></div></div></article><article class=\"border-b border-separator transition-all duration-700 ease-out cursor-pointer opacity-0 translate-y-6  px-6 py-6\"><div class=\"flex gap-5\"><div class=\"shrink-0 rounded-sm overflow-hidden\" style=\"width:140px\"><div class=\"w-full flex items-center justify-center rounded-sm\" style=\"aspect-ratio:2 / 3;background:linear-gradient(160deg, hsl(108, 12%, 90%) 0%, hsl(138, 18%, 82%) 100%)\"><span class=\"text-text-secondary text-[15px] font-semibold text-center px-6 opacity-60\">Aftermath</span></div></div><div class=\"flex-1 min-w-0\"><h3 class=\"text-[22px] font-bold text-text-primary leading-tight\">Aftermath<span class=\"inline-flex gap-2 ml-2\"><span class=\"text-[11px] font-semibold text-accent bg-accent/10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full\">New</span></span></h3><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-secondary mt-1\">2014<!-- --> · <!-- -->4.8<!-- -->/10</p><p class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary mt-1\">Peter Engert</p><p class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary mt-2 leading-relaxed line-clamp-3\">Nine strangers hole up in a rural Texas farmhouse after nuclear bombs devastate the country. Edward Furlong plays one of...</p></div></div><div class=\"overflow-hidden transition-all duration-500 ease-out\" style=\"max-height:0;opacity:0\"><div class=\"pt-4\"><p class=\"text-[16px] text-text-primary leading-[1.6]\">Nine strangers hole up in a rural Texas farmhouse after nuclear bombs devastate the country. Edward Furlong plays one of the survivors as radiation sickness, dwindling supplies, and outside threats push the group toward savagery. This is the closest spiritual sibling to The Divide -- same nuclear apocalypse setup, same confined-group-descending-into-madness arc, same nihilistic ending. Lower budget but it commits fully to the bleakness.</p><blockquote class=\"mt-6 pl-4 border-l-2 border-accent\"><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-secondary leading-relaxed italic\">“<!-- -->Less a story of survival than a bare-bones morality drama on the different ways in which the end might be faced. Unflinching.<!-- -->”</p></blockquote><blockquote class=\"mt-3 pl-4 border-l-2 border-separator\"><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-secondary leading-relaxed italic\">“<!-- -->Bargain-bin Divide with none of the performances to back it up. Furlong sleepwalks through it.<!-- -->”</p></blockquote><div class=\"mt-4\"><p class=\"text-[12px] font-semibold text-text-secondary uppercase tracking-wider mb-2\">Where to watch</p><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-primary\"><span class=\"text-accent font-medium\">Free: </span>Tubi, Plex, Hoopla</p><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-primary mt-1\"><span class=\"text-text-secondary\">Rent/Buy: </span>Amazon Video, Apple TV, Vudu</p></div><div class=\"mt-5 flex items-center gap-4\"><button class=\"flex items-center gap-1.5 py-1 transition-opacity hover:opacity-70\" aria-label=\"Save\"><svg width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#6E6E73\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\"><path d=\"M5 4a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h10a2 2 0 0 1 2 2v18l-7-4-7 4V4z\"></path></svg><span class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary\">Save for later</span></button><button class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary hover:text-text-primary transition-colors py-1\">Already seen</button><button class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary hover:text-text-primary transition-colors py-1\">Not for me</button></div></div></div></article><article class=\"border-b border-separator transition-all duration-700 ease-out cursor-pointer opacity-0 translate-y-6 \"><div class=\"w-full flex items-center justify-center \" style=\"aspect-ratio:16 / 9;background:linear-gradient(160deg, hsl(358, 12%, 90%) 0%, hsl(28, 18%, 82%) 100%)\"><span class=\"text-text-secondary text-[15px] font-semibold text-center px-6 opacity-60\">Hidden</span></div><div class=\"px-6 py-6\"><h3 class=\"text-[28px] font-bold text-text-primary leading-tight\">Hidden<span class=\"inline-flex gap-2 ml-2\"><span class=\"text-[11px] font-semibold text-accent bg-accent/10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full\">New</span></span></h3><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-secondary mt-1\">2015<!-- --> · <!-- -->6.4<!-- -->/10</p><p class=\"text-[15px] text-text-secondary mt-2 leading-relaxed\">Before Stranger Things, the Duffer Brothers made this tight bunker thriller about a family of three surviving undergroun...</p><div class=\"overflow-hidden transition-all duration-500 ease-out\" style=\"max-height:0;opacity:0\"><div class=\"pt-4\"><p class=\"text-[16px] text-text-primary leading-[1.6]\">Before Stranger Things, the Duffer Brothers made this tight bunker thriller about a family of three surviving underground after an outbreak called &#x27;the Breathers&#x27; devastated the surface. Alexander Skarsgard and Andrea Riseborough deliver restrained performances in an increasingly claustrophobic fallout shelter. The film methodically reveals its hand, and the final-act twist recontextualizes everything -- much like how The Divide slowly peels back layers of who these people really are. Genuinely underrated.</p><blockquote class=\"mt-6 pl-4 border-l-2 border-accent\"><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-secondary leading-relaxed italic\">“<!-- -->A tightly written story with balanced, well-acted characters and a twist that actually earns its shock. The Duffer Brothers&#x27; best work.<!-- -->”</p></blockquote><blockquote class=\"mt-3 pl-4 border-l-2 border-separator\"><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-secondary leading-relaxed italic\">“<!-- -->Too slow for what it is. The twist is clever but doesn&#x27;t fully land because the middle section drags.<!-- -->”</p></blockquote><div class=\"mt-4\"><p class=\"text-[12px] font-semibold text-text-secondary uppercase tracking-wider mb-2\">Where to watch</p><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-primary mt-1\"><span class=\"text-text-secondary\">Rent/Buy: </span>Amazon Video, Apple TV, Fandango At Home</p></div><div class=\"mt-5 flex items-center gap-4\"><button class=\"flex items-center gap-1.5 py-1 transition-opacity hover:opacity-70\" aria-label=\"Save\"><svg width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#6E6E73\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\"><path d=\"M5 4a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h10a2 2 0 0 1 2 2v18l-7-4-7 4V4z\"></path></svg><span class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary\">Save for later</span></button><button class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary hover:text-text-primary transition-colors py-1\">Already seen</button><button class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary hover:text-text-primary transition-colors py-1\">Not for me</button></div></div></div></div></article><article class=\"border-b border-separator transition-all duration-700 ease-out cursor-pointer opacity-0 translate-y-6  px-6 py-8\"><h3 class=\"text-[28px] font-bold text-text-primary leading-tight\">The Day<span class=\"inline-flex gap-2 ml-2\"><span class=\"text-[11px] font-semibold text-accent bg-accent/10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full\">New</span></span></h3><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-secondary mt-1\">2011<!-- --> · <!-- -->5.3<!-- -->/10</p><p class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary mt-1\">Douglas Aarniokoski</p><p class=\"text-[15px] text-text-secondary mt-3 leading-relaxed\">Five survivors in a post-apocalyptic wasteland barricade themselves in a farmhouse, only to discover they&#x27;ve stumbled in...</p><div class=\"overflow-hidden transition-all duration-500 ease-out\" style=\"max-height:0;opacity:0\"><div class=\"pt-4\"><p class=\"text-[16px] text-text-primary leading-[1.6]\">Five survivors in a post-apocalyptic wasteland barricade themselves in a farmhouse, only to discover they&#x27;ve stumbled into a trap set by cannibals. The desaturated, almost monochrome visual style mirrors The Divide&#x27;s grimy aesthetic. Like The Divide, the real horror isn&#x27;t the external threat but the fractures within the group -- trust disintegrates, alliances shift, and the veneer of cooperation cracks under the weight of survival. The home-invasion-in-reverse structure keeps the tension relentless.</p><blockquote class=\"mt-6 pl-4 border-l-2 border-accent\"><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-secondary leading-relaxed italic\">“<!-- -->A taut post-apocalyptic horror with a clever twist on the home invasion formula. The washed-out look works perfectly.<!-- -->”</p></blockquote><blockquote class=\"mt-3 pl-4 border-l-2 border-separator\"><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-secondary leading-relaxed italic\">“<!-- -->Basic survivor group vs cannibals setup done competently but without any real depth or surprises.<!-- -->”</p></blockquote><div class=\"mt-4\"><p class=\"text-[12px] font-semibold text-text-secondary uppercase tracking-wider mb-2\">Where to watch</p><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-primary\"><span class=\"text-accent font-medium\">Free: </span>Plex, Fandango At Home Free, Hoopla</p><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-primary mt-1\"><span class=\"text-text-secondary\">Streaming: </span>Amazon Prime Video</p><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-primary mt-1\"><span class=\"text-text-secondary\">Rent/Buy: </span>Amazon Video</p></div><div class=\"mt-5 flex items-center gap-4\"><button class=\"flex items-center gap-1.5 py-1 transition-opacity hover:opacity-70\" aria-label=\"Save\"><svg width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#6E6E73\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\"><path d=\"M5 4a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h10a2 2 0 0 1 2 2v18l-7-4-7 4V4z\"></path></svg><span class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary\">Save for later</span></button><button class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary hover:text-text-primary transition-colors py-1\">Already seen</button><button class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary hover:text-text-primary transition-colors py-1\">Not for me</button></div></div></div></article><article class=\"border-b border-separator transition-all duration-700 ease-out cursor-pointer opacity-0 translate-y-6 \"><div class=\"w-full flex items-center justify-center \" style=\"aspect-ratio:2 / 3;background:linear-gradient(160deg, hsl(243, 12%, 90%) 0%, hsl(273, 18%, 82%) 100%)\"><span class=\"text-text-secondary text-[15px] font-semibold text-center px-6 opacity-60\">Await Further Instructions</span></div><div class=\"px-6 py-6\"><h3 class=\"text-[28px] font-bold text-text-primary leading-tight\">Await Further Instructions<span class=\"inline-flex gap-2 ml-2\"><span class=\"text-[11px] font-semibold text-accent bg-accent/10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full\">New</span></span></h3><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-secondary mt-1\">2018<!-- --> · <!-- -->4.9<!-- -->/10</p><p class=\"text-[15px] text-text-secondary mt-2 leading-relaxed\">A dysfunctional family wakes up on Christmas to find their house sealed by a mysterious black membrane. Cryptic instruct...</p><div class=\"overflow-hidden transition-all duration-500 ease-out\" style=\"max-height:0;opacity:0\"><div class=\"pt-4\"><p class=\"text-[16px] text-text-primary leading-[1.6]\">A dysfunctional family wakes up on Christmas to find their house sealed by a mysterious black membrane. Cryptic instructions appear on the TV, and as they comply, paranoia and power struggles tear the family apart. This is The Divide&#x27;s DNA in a domestic setting -- a confined group turning on each other as an outside force applies pressure. The social commentary on authoritarianism and blind obedience hits hard. The body horror in the final act goes to genuinely disturbing places.</p><blockquote class=\"mt-6 pl-4 border-l-2 border-accent\"><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-secondary leading-relaxed italic\">“<!-- -->A mind-bending sci-fi thriller that uses family dysfunction as a pressure cooker. The escalation is genuinely unnerving.<!-- -->”</p></blockquote><blockquote class=\"mt-3 pl-4 border-l-2 border-separator\"><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-secondary leading-relaxed italic\">“<!-- -->The message about media compliance is about as subtle as a sledgehammer. Characters are too stupid to root for.<!-- -->”</p></blockquote><div class=\"mt-4\"><p class=\"text-[12px] font-semibold text-text-secondary uppercase tracking-wider mb-2\">Where to watch</p><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-primary\"><span class=\"text-accent font-medium\">Free: </span>Roku Channel, Pluto TV, Fandango At Home Free</p><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-primary mt-1\"><span class=\"text-text-secondary\">Streaming: </span>Amazon Prime Video, Shudder</p><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-primary mt-1\"><span class=\"text-text-secondary\">Rent/Buy: </span>Amazon Video, Apple TV</p></div><div class=\"mt-5 flex items-center gap-4\"><button class=\"flex items-center gap-1.5 py-1 transition-opacity hover:opacity-70\" aria-label=\"Save\"><svg width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#6E6E73\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\"><path d=\"M5 4a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h10a2 2 0 0 1 2 2v18l-7-4-7 4V4z\"></path></svg><span class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary\">Save for later</span></button><button class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary hover:text-text-primary transition-colors py-1\">Already seen</button><button class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary hover:text-text-primary transition-colors py-1\">Not for me</button></div></div></div></div></article><section class=\"py-16 px-6\"><div class=\"max-w-2xl mx-auto text-center transition-all duration-700 ease-out opacity-0 translate-y-4\"><div class=\"relative inline-block\"><svg class=\"absolute -left-8 top-1/2 -translate-y-1/2\" width=\"20\" height=\"48\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 48\" fill=\"none\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\"><path d=\"M16 4C8 6 5 14 4 24C5 34 8 42 16 44\" stroke=\"#0496FF\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" fill=\"none\"></path></svg><svg class=\"absolute -right-8 top-1/2 -translate-y-1/2\" width=\"20\" height=\"48\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 48\" fill=\"none\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\"><path d=\"M4 4C12 6 15 14 16 24C15 34 12 42 4 44\" stroke=\"#0496FF\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" fill=\"none\"></path></svg><h3 class=\"text-[28px] font-bold text-text-primary px-4\">Sealed in</h3></div><p class=\"text-[14px] font-normal text-text-secondary mt-3\">Bunkers, shelters, and nowhere to go</p></div></section><article class=\"border-b border-separator transition-all duration-700 ease-out cursor-pointer opacity-0 translate-y-6  px-6 py-6\"><div class=\"flex gap-5\"><div class=\"shrink-0 rounded-sm overflow-hidden\" style=\"width:140px\"><div class=\"w-full flex items-center justify-center rounded-sm\" style=\"aspect-ratio:2 / 3;background:linear-gradient(160deg, hsl(149, 12%, 90%) 0%, hsl(179, 18%, 82%) 100%)\"><span class=\"text-text-secondary text-[15px] font-semibold text-center px-6 opacity-60\">Hunger</span></div></div><div class=\"flex-1 min-w-0\"><h3 class=\"text-[22px] font-bold text-text-primary leading-tight\">Hunger<span class=\"inline-flex gap-2 ml-2\"><span class=\"text-[11px] font-semibold text-accent bg-accent/10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full\">New</span></span></h3><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-secondary mt-1\">2009<!-- --> · <!-- -->5.2<!-- -->/10</p><p class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary mt-1\">Steven Hentges</p><p class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary mt-2 leading-relaxed line-clamp-3\">Five strangers are abducted and imprisoned in an underground dungeon with no food and a countdown clock. The experiment ...</p></div></div><div class=\"overflow-hidden transition-all duration-500 ease-out\" style=\"max-height:0;opacity:0\"><div class=\"pt-4\"><p class=\"text-[16px] text-text-primary leading-[1.6]\">Five strangers are abducted and imprisoned in an underground dungeon with no food and a countdown clock. The experiment is simple: how long before they start eating each other? This is the purest distillation of The Divide&#x27;s central question about what humans will do when pushed past the breaking point. The gradual psychological breakdown is methodical and unflinching. It&#x27;s a grueling watch -- not because of graphic content, but because of the slow inevitability of what&#x27;s coming.</p><blockquote class=\"mt-6 pl-4 border-l-2 border-accent\"><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-secondary leading-relaxed italic\">“<!-- -->Takes a simple premise and mines it for genuine psychological horror. The descent is patient and deeply uncomfortable.<!-- -->”</p></blockquote><blockquote class=\"mt-3 pl-4 border-l-2 border-separator\"><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-secondary leading-relaxed italic\">“<!-- -->A one-note exercise in misery. Once you know the premise, there are no surprises -- just waiting for the inevitable.<!-- -->”</p></blockquote><div class=\"mt-4\"><p class=\"text-[12px] font-semibold text-text-secondary uppercase tracking-wider mb-2\">Where to watch</p><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-primary\"><span class=\"text-accent font-medium\">Free: </span>Tubi, Roku Channel</p><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-primary mt-1\"><span class=\"text-text-secondary\">Rent/Buy: </span>Amazon Video</p></div><div class=\"mt-5 flex items-center gap-4\"><button class=\"flex items-center gap-1.5 py-1 transition-opacity hover:opacity-70\" aria-label=\"Save\"><svg width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#6E6E73\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\"><path d=\"M5 4a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h10a2 2 0 0 1 2 2v18l-7-4-7 4V4z\"></path></svg><span class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary\">Save for later</span></button><button class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary hover:text-text-primary transition-colors py-1\">Already seen</button><button class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary hover:text-text-primary transition-colors py-1\">Not for me</button></div></div></div></article><article class=\"border-b border-separator transition-all duration-700 ease-out cursor-pointer opacity-0 translate-y-6 \"><div class=\"w-full flex items-center justify-center \" style=\"aspect-ratio:16 / 9;background:linear-gradient(160deg, hsl(130, 12%, 90%) 0%, hsl(160, 18%, 82%) 100%)\"><span class=\"text-text-secondary text-[15px] font-semibold text-center px-6 opacity-60\">We Need to Do Something</span></div><div class=\"px-6 py-6\"><h3 class=\"text-[28px] font-bold text-text-primary leading-tight\">We Need to Do Something<span class=\"inline-flex gap-2 ml-2\"><span class=\"text-[11px] font-semibold text-accent bg-accent/10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full\">New</span></span></h3><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-secondary mt-1\">2021<!-- --> · <!-- -->4.5<!-- -->/10</p><p class=\"text-[15px] text-text-secondary mt-2 leading-relaxed\">A family of four takes shelter in their bathroom during a tornado. A fallen tree blocks the door. Days pass. No one come...</p><div class=\"overflow-hidden transition-all duration-500 ease-out\" style=\"max-height:0;opacity:0\"><div class=\"pt-4\"><p class=\"text-[16px] text-text-primary leading-[1.6]\">A family of four takes shelter in their bathroom during a tornado. A fallen tree blocks the door. Days pass. No one comes. As dehydration and hunger set in, the family&#x27;s dysfunction erupts -- the abusive father, the guilty teenager hiding a dark secret, the mother trying to hold it together. Strange and terrifying things begin happening outside the door. Like The Divide, it uses catastrophe as the catalyst for human ugliness to surface, but adds an occult layer that pushes it into genuinely weird territory. The bathroom setting is oppressively small.</p><blockquote class=\"mt-6 pl-4 border-l-2 border-accent\"><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-secondary leading-relaxed italic\">“<!-- -->Wildly ambitious for a single-room horror. The practical effects are disgusting in the best way, and the family dynamics feel painfully real.<!-- -->”</p></blockquote><blockquote class=\"mt-3 pl-4 border-l-2 border-separator\"><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-secondary leading-relaxed italic\">“<!-- -->An absolute mess that can&#x27;t decide if it wants to be a family drama or Lovecraftian horror. The ending is nonsensical.<!-- -->”</p></blockquote><div class=\"mt-4\"><p class=\"text-[12px] font-semibold text-text-secondary uppercase tracking-wider mb-2\">Where to watch</p><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-primary\"><span class=\"text-accent font-medium\">Free: </span>Kanopy</p><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-primary mt-1\"><span class=\"text-text-secondary\">Streaming: </span>AMC+, Sundance Now, Philo</p><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-primary mt-1\"><span class=\"text-text-secondary\">Rent/Buy: </span>Apple TV, Amazon Video, Fandango At Home</p></div><div class=\"mt-5 flex items-center gap-4\"><button class=\"flex items-center gap-1.5 py-1 transition-opacity hover:opacity-70\" aria-label=\"Save\"><svg width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#6E6E73\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\"><path d=\"M5 4a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h10a2 2 0 0 1 2 2v18l-7-4-7 4V4z\"></path></svg><span class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary\">Save for later</span></button><button class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary hover:text-text-primary transition-colors py-1\">Already seen</button><button class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary hover:text-text-primary transition-colors py-1\">Not for me</button></div></div></div></div></article><article class=\"border-b border-separator transition-all duration-700 ease-out cursor-pointer opacity-0 translate-y-6  px-6 py-8\"><h3 class=\"text-[28px] font-bold text-text-primary leading-tight\">The Killing Room<span class=\"inline-flex gap-2 ml-2\"><span class=\"text-[11px] font-semibold text-accent bg-accent/10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full\">New</span></span></h3><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-secondary mt-1\">2009<!-- --> · <!-- -->5.6<!-- -->/10</p><p class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary mt-1\">Jonathan Liebesman</p><p class=\"text-[15px] text-text-secondary mt-3 leading-relaxed\">Four volunteers sign up for what they think is a simple psychological study. They&#x27;re locked in a white room. Then one of...</p><div class=\"overflow-hidden transition-all duration-500 ease-out\" style=\"max-height:0;opacity:0\"><div class=\"pt-4\"><p class=\"text-[16px] text-text-primary leading-[1.6]\">Four volunteers sign up for what they think is a simple psychological study. They&#x27;re locked in a white room. Then one of them is shot in the head. The study is real: a classified government program testing who breaks and who endures. Timothy Hutton, Clea DuVall, and Peter Stormare bring gravitas to a premise that could have been pulpy. Like The Divide, the horror comes from watching ordinary people subjected to extraordinary pressure, with authority figures pulling the strings from behind glass.</p><blockquote class=\"mt-6 pl-4 border-l-2 border-accent\"><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-secondary leading-relaxed italic\">“<!-- -->Taut, well-acted thriller that earns its paranoia. Stormare is chilling as always. The MKUltra angle adds historical weight.<!-- -->”</p></blockquote><blockquote class=\"mt-3 pl-4 border-l-2 border-separator\"><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-secondary leading-relaxed italic\">“<!-- -->Starts strong but the third act reveals are predictable. The government conspiracy angle is half-baked.<!-- -->”</p></blockquote><div class=\"mt-4\"><p class=\"text-[12px] font-semibold text-text-secondary uppercase tracking-wider mb-2\">Where to watch</p><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-primary mt-1\"><span class=\"text-text-secondary\">Rent/Buy: </span>Amazon Video, Apple TV</p></div><div class=\"mt-5 flex items-center gap-4\"><button class=\"flex items-center gap-1.5 py-1 transition-opacity hover:opacity-70\" aria-label=\"Save\"><svg width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#6E6E73\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\"><path d=\"M5 4a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h10a2 2 0 0 1 2 2v18l-7-4-7 4V4z\"></path></svg><span class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary\">Save for later</span></button><button class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary hover:text-text-primary transition-colors py-1\">Already seen</button><button class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary hover:text-text-primary transition-colors py-1\">Not for me</button></div></div></div></article><article class=\"border-b border-separator transition-all duration-700 ease-out cursor-pointer opacity-0 translate-y-6 \"><div class=\"w-full flex items-center justify-center \" style=\"aspect-ratio:2 / 3;background:linear-gradient(160deg, hsl(218, 12%, 90%) 0%, hsl(248, 18%, 82%) 100%)\"><span class=\"text-text-secondary text-[15px] font-semibold text-center px-6 opacity-60\">Gehenna: Where Death Lives</span></div><div class=\"px-6 py-6\"><h3 class=\"text-[28px] font-bold text-text-primary leading-tight\">Gehenna: Where Death Lives<span class=\"inline-flex gap-2 ml-2\"><span class=\"text-[11px] font-semibold text-accent bg-accent/10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full\">New</span></span></h3><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-secondary mt-1\">2016<!-- --> · <!-- -->4.9<!-- -->/10</p><p class=\"text-[15px] text-text-secondary mt-2 leading-relaxed\">A resort development team in Saipan discovers an old Japanese WWII bunker during a site survey and descends inside. The ...</p><div class=\"overflow-hidden transition-all duration-500 ease-out\" style=\"max-height:0;opacity:0\"><div class=\"pt-4\"><p class=\"text-[16px] text-text-primary leading-[1.6]\">A resort development team in Saipan discovers an old Japanese WWII bunker during a site survey and descends inside. The bunker has its own rules -- time works differently, an ancient evil lurks, and the group begins to fracture. Recommended directly on the r/horror thread about movies like The Divide, this one combines the confined underground setting with supernatural elements. The bunker itself is a character, and the group dynamics under pressure deliver genuine tension even when the creature effects are uneven.</p><blockquote class=\"mt-6 pl-4 border-l-2 border-accent\"><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-secondary leading-relaxed italic\">“<!-- -->A genuinely creepy bunker horror that uses its Saipan setting and WWII history to elevate standard genre fare. The old man is terrifying.<!-- -->”</p></blockquote><blockquote class=\"mt-3 pl-4 border-l-2 border-separator\"><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-secondary leading-relaxed italic\">“<!-- -->Decent first half that falls apart once the monster fully reveals itself. The time-loop element is undercooked.<!-- -->”</p></blockquote><div class=\"mt-4\"><p class=\"text-[12px] font-semibold text-text-secondary uppercase tracking-wider mb-2\">Where to watch</p><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-primary mt-1\"><span class=\"text-text-secondary\">Rent/Buy: </span>Amazon Video</p></div><div class=\"mt-5 flex items-center gap-4\"><button class=\"flex items-center gap-1.5 py-1 transition-opacity hover:opacity-70\" aria-label=\"Save\"><svg width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#6E6E73\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\"><path d=\"M5 4a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h10a2 2 0 0 1 2 2v18l-7-4-7 4V4z\"></path></svg><span class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary\">Save for later</span></button><button class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary hover:text-text-primary transition-colors py-1\">Already seen</button><button class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary hover:text-text-primary transition-colors py-1\">Not for me</button></div></div></div></div></article><article class=\"border-b border-separator transition-all duration-700 ease-out cursor-pointer opacity-0 translate-y-6  px-6 py-6\"><div class=\"flex gap-5\"><div class=\"shrink-0 rounded-sm overflow-hidden\" style=\"width:140px\"><div class=\"w-full flex items-center justify-center rounded-sm\" style=\"aspect-ratio:2 / 3;background:linear-gradient(160deg, hsl(284, 12%, 90%) 0%, hsl(314, 18%, 82%) 100%)\"><span class=\"text-text-secondary text-[15px] font-semibold text-center px-6 opacity-60\">Mine 9</span></div></div><div class=\"flex-1 min-w-0\"><h3 class=\"text-[22px] font-bold text-text-primary leading-tight\">Mine 9<span class=\"inline-flex gap-2 ml-2\"><span class=\"text-[11px] font-semibold text-accent bg-accent/10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full\">New</span></span></h3><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-secondary mt-1\">2019<!-- --> · <!-- -->6<!-- -->/10</p><p class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary mt-1\">Eddie Mensore</p><p class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary mt-2 leading-relaxed line-clamp-3\">Nine Appalachian coal miners are trapped 2 miles underground after a methane explosion. With limited oxygen and no certa...</p></div></div><div class=\"overflow-hidden transition-all duration-500 ease-out\" style=\"max-height:0;opacity:0\"><div class=\"pt-4\"><p class=\"text-[16px] text-text-primary leading-[1.6]\">Nine Appalachian coal miners are trapped 2 miles underground after a methane explosion. With limited oxygen and no certainty of rescue, the group must navigate flooded tunnels and failing equipment while holding together psychologically. Shot with documentary-level realism in real coal mines, this is survival horror stripped of all genre artifice. Like The Divide, it&#x27;s about a group in a hole deciding whether cooperation or self-preservation wins. The Appalachian setting adds class-conscious weight -- these men were already trapped by economics before the mine sealed them in.</p><blockquote class=\"mt-6 pl-4 border-l-2 border-accent\"><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-secondary leading-relaxed italic\">“<!-- -->Shot with intense realism in actual coal mines. The claustrophobia is physical and the performances are lived-in.<!-- -->”</p></blockquote><blockquote class=\"mt-3 pl-4 border-l-2 border-separator\"><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-secondary leading-relaxed italic\">“<!-- -->Gritty and well-intentioned but dramatically inert. The miners are too noble for the film to find any real tension.<!-- -->”</p></blockquote><div class=\"mt-4\"><p class=\"text-[12px] font-semibold text-text-secondary uppercase tracking-wider mb-2\">Where to watch</p><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-primary\"><span class=\"text-accent font-medium\">Free: </span>Kanopy</p><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-primary mt-1\"><span class=\"text-text-secondary\">Rent/Buy: </span>Amazon Video</p></div><div class=\"mt-5 flex items-center gap-4\"><button class=\"flex items-center gap-1.5 py-1 transition-opacity hover:opacity-70\" aria-label=\"Save\"><svg width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#6E6E73\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\"><path d=\"M5 4a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h10a2 2 0 0 1 2 2v18l-7-4-7 4V4z\"></path></svg><span class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary\">Save for later</span></button><button class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary hover:text-text-primary transition-colors py-1\">Already seen</button><button class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary hover:text-text-primary transition-colors py-1\">Not for me</button></div></div></div></article><section class=\"py-16 px-6\"><div class=\"max-w-2xl mx-auto text-center transition-all duration-700 ease-out opacity-0 translate-y-4\"><div class=\"relative inline-block\"><svg class=\"absolute -left-8 top-1/2 -translate-y-1/2\" width=\"20\" height=\"48\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 48\" fill=\"none\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\"><path d=\"M16 4C8 6 5 14 4 24C5 34 8 42 16 44\" stroke=\"#0496FF\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" fill=\"none\"></path></svg><svg class=\"absolute -right-8 top-1/2 -translate-y-1/2\" width=\"20\" height=\"48\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 48\" fill=\"none\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\"><path d=\"M4 4C12 6 15 14 16 24C15 34 12 42 4 44\" stroke=\"#0496FF\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" fill=\"none\"></path></svg><h3 class=\"text-[28px] font-bold text-text-primary px-4\">Slow rot</h3></div><p class=\"text-[14px] font-normal text-text-secondary mt-3\">Dread that builds by the frame</p></div></section><article class=\"border-b border-separator transition-all duration-700 ease-out cursor-pointer opacity-0 translate-y-6 \"><div class=\"w-full flex items-center justify-center \" style=\"aspect-ratio:16 / 9;background:linear-gradient(160deg, hsl(12, 12%, 90%) 0%, hsl(42, 18%, 82%) 100%)\"><span class=\"text-text-secondary text-[15px] font-semibold text-center px-6 opacity-60\">Would You Rather</span></div><div class=\"px-6 py-6\"><h3 class=\"text-[28px] font-bold text-text-primary leading-tight\">Would You Rather<span class=\"inline-flex gap-2 ml-2\"><span class=\"text-[11px] font-semibold text-accent bg-accent/10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full\">New</span></span></h3><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-secondary mt-1\">2012<!-- --> · <!-- -->5.7<!-- -->/10</p><p class=\"text-[15px] text-text-secondary mt-2 leading-relaxed\">Eight desperate people accept a dinner invitation from a wealthy aristocrat played by Jeffrey Combs. The game: &#x27;Would Yo...</p><div class=\"overflow-hidden transition-all duration-500 ease-out\" style=\"max-height:0;opacity:0\"><div class=\"pt-4\"><p class=\"text-[16px] text-text-primary leading-[1.6]\">Eight desperate people accept a dinner invitation from a wealthy aristocrat played by Jeffrey Combs. The game: &#x27;Would You Rather&#x27; with lethal stakes. Each round forces participants to choose between inflicting pain on themselves or others. Like The Divide&#x27;s power dynamics, a sadistic authority figure controls the environment while the captives reveal their true natures. Brittany Snow anchors the film with genuine vulnerability, and Combs chews scenery with aristocratic menace. The ending is mercilessly bleak.</p><blockquote class=\"mt-6 pl-4 border-l-2 border-accent\"><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-secondary leading-relaxed italic\">“<!-- -->Jeffrey Combs elevates everything he&#x27;s in. The dinner party format keeps things tight and the final scene is a genuine gut-punch.<!-- -->”</p></blockquote><blockquote class=\"mt-3 pl-4 border-l-2 border-separator\"><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-secondary leading-relaxed italic\">“<!-- -->Diet Saw with a dinner party veneer. The moral dilemmas are too obviously constructed to feel real.<!-- -->”</p></blockquote><div class=\"mt-4\"><p class=\"text-[12px] font-semibold text-text-secondary uppercase tracking-wider mb-2\">Where to watch</p><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-primary\"><span class=\"text-accent font-medium\">Free: </span>Tubi, Kanopy</p><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-primary mt-1\"><span class=\"text-text-secondary\">Streaming: </span>Hulu, Shudder, Paramount+, Philo</p><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-primary mt-1\"><span class=\"text-text-secondary\">Rent/Buy: </span>Amazon Video, Apple TV, Fandango At Home</p></div><div class=\"mt-5 flex items-center gap-4\"><button class=\"flex items-center gap-1.5 py-1 transition-opacity hover:opacity-70\" aria-label=\"Save\"><svg width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#6E6E73\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\"><path d=\"M5 4a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h10a2 2 0 0 1 2 2v18l-7-4-7 4V4z\"></path></svg><span class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary\">Save for later</span></button><button class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary hover:text-text-primary transition-colors py-1\">Already seen</button><button class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary hover:text-text-primary transition-colors py-1\">Not for me</button></div></div></div></div></article><article class=\"border-b border-separator transition-all duration-700 ease-out cursor-pointer opacity-0 translate-y-6  px-6 py-8\"><h3 class=\"text-[28px] font-bold text-text-primary leading-tight\">Vile<span class=\"inline-flex gap-2 ml-2\"><span class=\"text-[11px] font-semibold text-accent bg-accent/10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full\">New</span></span></h3><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-secondary mt-1\">2011<!-- --> · <!-- -->4.8<!-- -->/10</p><p class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary mt-1\">Taylor Sheridan</p><p class=\"text-[15px] text-text-secondary mt-3 leading-relaxed\">A group of friends are kidnapped and locked in a house with vials attached to their brainstems. To fill the vials and un...</p><div class=\"overflow-hidden transition-all duration-500 ease-out\" style=\"max-height:0;opacity:0\"><div class=\"pt-4\"><p class=\"text-[16px] text-text-primary leading-[1.6]\">A group of friends are kidnapped and locked in a house with vials attached to their brainstems. To fill the vials and unlock the doors, they must trigger their bodies to produce certain chemicals -- through extreme pain. The catch: they have to inflict it on each other. This is The Divide&#x27;s group-turning-on-each-other premise distilled to its purest form. Rough edges but genuine tension in watching ordinary people negotiate who suffers and how much. The premise forces real moral horror out of its low budget.</p><blockquote class=\"mt-6 pl-4 border-l-2 border-accent\"><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-secondary leading-relaxed italic\">“<!-- -->A nasty little film that finds tension in the negotiations between captives. The premise forces genuine moral horror.<!-- -->”</p></blockquote><blockquote class=\"mt-3 pl-4 border-l-2 border-separator\"><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-secondary leading-relaxed italic\">“<!-- -->Bottom-shelf torture porn with zero character development. The Saw influence is too naked to feel original.<!-- -->”</p></blockquote><div class=\"mt-4\"><p class=\"text-[12px] font-semibold text-text-secondary uppercase tracking-wider mb-2\">Where to watch</p><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-primary\"><span class=\"text-accent font-medium\">Free: </span>Tubi, Plex, Hoopla, Kanopy</p><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-primary mt-1\"><span class=\"text-text-secondary\">Rent/Buy: </span>Amazon Video</p></div><div class=\"mt-5 flex items-center gap-4\"><button class=\"flex items-center gap-1.5 py-1 transition-opacity hover:opacity-70\" aria-label=\"Save\"><svg width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#6E6E73\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\"><path d=\"M5 4a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h10a2 2 0 0 1 2 2v18l-7-4-7 4V4z\"></path></svg><span class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary\">Save for later</span></button><button class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary hover:text-text-primary transition-colors py-1\">Already seen</button><button class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary hover:text-text-primary transition-colors py-1\">Not for me</button></div></div></div></article><article class=\"border-b border-separator transition-all duration-700 ease-out cursor-pointer opacity-0 translate-y-6 \"><div class=\"w-full flex items-center justify-center \" style=\"aspect-ratio:2 / 3;background:linear-gradient(160deg, hsl(256, 12%, 90%) 0%, hsl(286, 18%, 82%) 100%)\"><span class=\"text-text-secondary text-[15px] font-semibold text-center px-6 opacity-60\">House of 9</span></div><div class=\"px-6 py-6\"><h3 class=\"text-[28px] font-bold text-text-primary leading-tight\">House of 9<span class=\"inline-flex gap-2 ml-2\"><span class=\"text-[11px] font-semibold text-accent bg-accent/10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full\">New</span></span></h3><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-secondary mt-1\">2005<!-- --> · <!-- -->5.3<!-- -->/10</p><p class=\"text-[15px] text-text-secondary mt-2 leading-relaxed\">Nine strangers -- including a priest, a cop, a dancer, and a tennis player -- are drugged, kidnapped, and locked in a ho...</p><div class=\"overflow-hidden transition-all duration-500 ease-out\" style=\"max-height:0;opacity:0\"><div class=\"pt-4\"><p class=\"text-[16px] text-text-primary leading-[1.6]\">Nine strangers -- including a priest, a cop, a dancer, and a tennis player -- are drugged, kidnapped, and locked in a house. A voice tells them the last one alive wins five million dollars. Dennis Hopper anchors the cast as the moral compass who slowly realizes morality has no currency here. This is pure Divide territory: diverse personalities stripped of societal roles and forced to negotiate survival in a sealed space. The kills escalate as alliances form and shatter. Hopper&#x27;s late-career commitment elevates what could have been disposable.</p><blockquote class=\"mt-6 pl-4 border-l-2 border-accent\"><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-secondary leading-relaxed italic\">“<!-- -->Dennis Hopper in a confined horror? Sign me up. He brings gravity to a premise that could have been trashy.<!-- -->”</p></blockquote><blockquote class=\"mt-3 pl-4 border-l-2 border-separator\"><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-secondary leading-relaxed italic\">“<!-- -->A Big Brother episode with murder. The characters are one-dimensional archetypes feeding a mechanical plot.<!-- -->”</p></blockquote><div class=\"mt-4\"><p class=\"text-[12px] font-semibold text-text-secondary uppercase tracking-wider mb-2\">Where to watch</p><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-primary\"><span class=\"text-accent font-medium\">Free: </span>Tubi, Plex, Hoopla, Roku Channel</p><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-primary mt-1\"><span class=\"text-text-secondary\">Streaming: </span>Amazon Prime Video</p><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-primary mt-1\"><span class=\"text-text-secondary\">Rent/Buy: </span>Amazon Video, Apple TV, Fandango At Home</p></div><div class=\"mt-5 flex items-center gap-4\"><button class=\"flex items-center gap-1.5 py-1 transition-opacity hover:opacity-70\" aria-label=\"Save\"><svg width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#6E6E73\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\"><path d=\"M5 4a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h10a2 2 0 0 1 2 2v18l-7-4-7 4V4z\"></path></svg><span class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary\">Save for later</span></button><button class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary hover:text-text-primary transition-colors py-1\">Already seen</button><button class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary hover:text-text-primary transition-colors py-1\">Not for me</button></div></div></div></div></article><article class=\"border-b border-separator transition-all duration-700 ease-out cursor-pointer opacity-0 translate-y-6  px-6 py-6\"><div class=\"flex gap-5\"><div class=\"shrink-0 rounded-sm overflow-hidden\" style=\"width:140px\"><div class=\"w-full flex items-center justify-center rounded-sm\" style=\"aspect-ratio:2 / 3;background:linear-gradient(160deg, hsl(204, 12%, 90%) 0%, hsl(234, 18%, 82%) 100%)\"><span class=\"text-text-secondary text-[15px] font-semibold text-center px-6 opacity-60\">Crawl or Die</span></div></div><div class=\"flex-1 min-w-0\"><h3 class=\"text-[22px] font-bold text-text-primary leading-tight\">Crawl or Die<span class=\"inline-flex gap-2 ml-2\"><span class=\"text-[11px] font-semibold text-accent bg-accent/10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full\">New</span></span></h3><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-secondary mt-1\">2014<!-- --> · <!-- -->4<!-- -->/10</p><p class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary mt-1\">Oklahoma Ward</p><p class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary mt-2 leading-relaxed line-clamp-3\">In a post-apocalyptic future, a special ops team must escort the last fertile woman on Earth through increasingly narrow...</p></div></div><div class=\"overflow-hidden transition-all duration-500 ease-out\" style=\"max-height:0;opacity:0\"><div class=\"pt-4\"><p class=\"text-[16px] text-text-primary leading-[1.6]\">In a post-apocalyptic future, a special ops team must escort the last fertile woman on Earth through increasingly narrow underground tunnels while being hunted by an alien creature. The tunnels get progressively tighter until characters can barely move -- this may be the most physically claustrophobic film ever made. Shot in real confined spaces with no CGI trickery. Like The Divide&#x27;s basement, the environment itself becomes the primary antagonist, squeezing both characters and audience to the breaking point. Micro-budget but utterly committed to its suffocating premise.</p><blockquote class=\"mt-6 pl-4 border-l-2 border-accent\"><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-secondary leading-relaxed italic\">“<!-- -->Definitely the most claustrophobic movie ever made. The shrinking tunnel concept is genius and the practical execution is jaw-dropping for the budget.<!-- -->”</p></blockquote><blockquote class=\"mt-3 pl-4 border-l-2 border-separator\"><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-secondary leading-relaxed italic\">“<!-- -->A massive snoozefest. A dwindling number of people crawling through confined spaces is the entire movie. That&#x27;s it.<!-- -->”</p></blockquote><div class=\"mt-4\"><p class=\"text-[12px] font-semibold text-text-secondary uppercase tracking-wider mb-2\">Where to watch</p><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-primary\"><span class=\"text-accent font-medium\">Free: </span>Tubi</p><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-primary mt-1\"><span class=\"text-text-secondary\">Rent/Buy: </span>Amazon Video</p></div><div class=\"mt-5 flex items-center gap-4\"><button class=\"flex items-center gap-1.5 py-1 transition-opacity hover:opacity-70\" aria-label=\"Save\"><svg width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#6E6E73\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\"><path d=\"M5 4a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h10a2 2 0 0 1 2 2v18l-7-4-7 4V4z\"></path></svg><span class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary\">Save for later</span></button><button class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary hover:text-text-primary transition-colors py-1\">Already seen</button><button class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary hover:text-text-primary transition-colors py-1\">Not for me</button></div></div></div></article><article class=\"border-b border-separator transition-all duration-700 ease-out cursor-pointer opacity-0 translate-y-6 \"><div class=\"w-full flex items-center justify-center \" style=\"aspect-ratio:16 / 9;background:linear-gradient(160deg, hsl(24, 12%, 90%) 0%, hsl(54, 18%, 82%) 100%)\"><span class=\"text-text-secondary text-[15px] font-semibold text-center px-6 opacity-60\">Circle</span></div><div class=\"px-6 py-6\"><h3 class=\"text-[28px] font-bold text-text-primary leading-tight\">Circle<span class=\"inline-flex gap-2 ml-2\"><span class=\"text-[11px] font-semibold text-accent bg-accent/10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full\">New</span></span></h3><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-secondary mt-1\">2015<!-- --> · <!-- -->6<!-- -->/10</p><p class=\"text-[15px] text-text-secondary mt-2 leading-relaxed\">Fifty strangers wake standing in a circle. Every two minutes, one person dies -- voted out by the group. If no consensus...</p><div class=\"overflow-hidden transition-all duration-500 ease-out\" style=\"max-height:0;opacity:0\"><div class=\"pt-4\"><p class=\"text-[16px] text-text-primary leading-[1.6]\">Fifty strangers wake standing in a circle. Every two minutes, one person dies -- voted out by the group. If no consensus, the orb in the center chooses randomly. What follows is a compressed simulation of societal collapse: racism, ageism, class warfare, and tribalism all surface as people argue for their lives. It&#x27;s The Divide&#x27;s group dynamics turned into a lethal debate club. No weapons, no physical violence -- just persuasion, manipulation, and the exposure of prejudice under existential pressure. The ending is cold.</p><blockquote class=\"mt-6 pl-4 border-l-2 border-accent\"><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-secondary leading-relaxed italic\">“<!-- -->A brilliant social experiment film that exposes how quickly people sort into tribes when survival is at stake. The debates feel chillingly authentic.<!-- -->”</p></blockquote><blockquote class=\"mt-3 pl-4 border-l-2 border-separator\"><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-secondary leading-relaxed italic\">“<!-- -->A 12 Angry Men knockoff with a sci-fi coat of paint. The moralizing is heavy-handed and the characters are mouthpieces.<!-- -->”</p></blockquote><div class=\"mt-4\"><p class=\"text-[12px] font-semibold text-text-secondary uppercase tracking-wider mb-2\">Where to watch</p><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-primary mt-1\"><span class=\"text-text-secondary\">Streaming: </span>Netflix</p><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-primary mt-1\"><span class=\"text-text-secondary\">Rent/Buy: </span>Amazon Video, Apple TV</p></div><div class=\"mt-5 flex items-center gap-4\"><button class=\"flex items-center gap-1.5 py-1 transition-opacity hover:opacity-70\" aria-label=\"Save\"><svg width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#6E6E73\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\"><path d=\"M5 4a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h10a2 2 0 0 1 2 2v18l-7-4-7 4V4z\"></path></svg><span class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary\">Save for later</span></button><button class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary hover:text-text-primary transition-colors py-1\">Already seen</button><button class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary hover:text-text-primary transition-colors py-1\">Not for me</button></div></div></div></div></article><section class=\"py-16 px-6\"><div class=\"max-w-2xl mx-auto text-center transition-all duration-700 ease-out opacity-0 translate-y-4\"><div class=\"relative inline-block\"><svg class=\"absolute -left-8 top-1/2 -translate-y-1/2\" width=\"20\" height=\"48\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 48\" fill=\"none\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\"><path d=\"M16 4C8 6 5 14 4 24C5 34 8 42 16 44\" stroke=\"#0496FF\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" fill=\"none\"></path></svg><svg class=\"absolute -right-8 top-1/2 -translate-y-1/2\" width=\"20\" height=\"48\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 48\" fill=\"none\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\"><path d=\"M4 4C12 6 15 14 16 24C15 34 12 42 4 44\" stroke=\"#0496FF\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" fill=\"none\"></path></svg><h3 class=\"text-[28px] font-bold text-text-primary px-4\">Sealed in</h3></div><p class=\"text-[14px] font-normal text-text-secondary mt-3\">Bunkers, shelters, and nowhere to go</p></div></section><article class=\"border-b border-separator transition-all duration-700 ease-out cursor-pointer opacity-0 translate-y-6  px-6 py-8\"><h3 class=\"text-[28px] font-bold text-text-primary leading-tight\">Dread<span class=\"inline-flex gap-2 ml-2\"><span class=\"text-[11px] font-semibold text-accent bg-accent/10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full\">New</span></span></h3><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-secondary mt-1\">2009<!-- --> · <!-- -->5.6<!-- -->/10</p><p class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary mt-1\">Anthony DiBlasi</p><p class=\"text-[15px] text-text-secondary mt-3 leading-relaxed\">Based on Clive Barker&#x27;s short story, three college students begin a &#x27;fear study&#x27; -- recording people discussing their de...</p><div class=\"overflow-hidden transition-all duration-500 ease-out\" style=\"max-height:0;opacity:0\"><div class=\"pt-4\"><p class=\"text-[16px] text-text-primary leading-[1.6]\">Based on Clive Barker&#x27;s short story, three college students begin a &#x27;fear study&#x27; -- recording people discussing their deepest dreads. But one of them, the unstable Quaid, isn&#x27;t interested in academic research. He wants to weaponize fear, pushing subjects into confronting their phobias in the most extreme ways imaginable. The film walks a razor line between psychological thriller and body horror, but what makes it Divide-adjacent is the power dynamic: one charismatic, damaged person gradually gaining control over others and stripping away their agency. The final act sequences are deeply personal cruelties -- not generic torture, but fears tailored to destroy specific people. Collider called it a film that &#x27;will make even hardcore horror fans squirm.&#x27; A Film Twitter staple in &#x27;underrated Barker adaptations&#x27; threads.</p><blockquote class=\"mt-6 pl-4 border-l-2 border-accent\"><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-secondary leading-relaxed italic\">“<!-- -->The most underrated Clive Barker adaptation. The fear is deeply personal, not mechanical -- each victim&#x27;s torment feels specifically designed to destroy them as individuals.<!-- -->”</p></blockquote><blockquote class=\"mt-3 pl-4 border-l-2 border-separator\"><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-secondary leading-relaxed italic\">“<!-- -->Overwritten and pretentious. Tries to pass off cruelty as philosophical depth but never earns the intellectual weight it claims.<!-- -->”</p></blockquote><div class=\"mt-4\"><p class=\"text-[12px] font-semibold text-text-secondary uppercase tracking-wider mb-2\">Where to watch</p><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-primary\"><span class=\"text-accent font-medium\">Free: </span>Tubi, Plex, Fawesome</p><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-primary mt-1\"><span class=\"text-text-secondary\">Rent/Buy: </span>Amazon Video, Fandango At Home</p></div><div class=\"mt-5 flex items-center gap-4\"><button class=\"flex items-center gap-1.5 py-1 transition-opacity hover:opacity-70\" aria-label=\"Save\"><svg width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#6E6E73\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\"><path d=\"M5 4a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h10a2 2 0 0 1 2 2v18l-7-4-7 4V4z\"></path></svg><span class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary\">Save for later</span></button><button class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary hover:text-text-primary transition-colors py-1\">Already seen</button><button class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary hover:text-text-primary transition-colors py-1\">Not for me</button></div></div></div></article><article class=\"border-b border-separator transition-all duration-700 ease-out cursor-pointer opacity-0 translate-y-6 \"><div class=\"w-full flex items-center justify-center \" style=\"aspect-ratio:2 / 3;background:linear-gradient(160deg, hsl(314, 12%, 90%) 0%, hsl(344, 18%, 82%) 100%)\"><span class=\"text-text-secondary text-[15px] font-semibold text-center px-6 opacity-60\">Air</span></div><div class=\"px-6 py-6\"><h3 class=\"text-[28px] font-bold text-text-primary leading-tight\">Air<span class=\"inline-flex gap-2 ml-2\"><span class=\"text-[11px] font-semibold text-accent bg-accent/10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full\">New</span></span></h3><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-secondary mt-1\">2015<!-- --> · <!-- -->5.1<!-- -->/10</p><p class=\"text-[15px] text-text-secondary mt-2 leading-relaxed\">After a biochemical disaster renders the atmosphere unbreathable, two custodial engineers (Norman Reedus and Djimon Houn...</p><div class=\"overflow-hidden transition-all duration-500 ease-out\" style=\"max-height:0;opacity:0\"><div class=\"pt-4\"><p class=\"text-[16px] text-text-primary leading-[1.6]\">After a biochemical disaster renders the atmosphere unbreathable, two custodial engineers (Norman Reedus and Djimon Hounsou) maintain an underground facility housing humanity&#x27;s last hope in cryogenic sleep. They wake every six months for brief maintenance shifts, then go back under. When equipment fails and oxygen runs low, the two men are forced to stay awake -- and the psychological pressure of deciding who lives and who dies in a bunker with finite air becomes unbearable. A two-hander from a video game designer (Christian Cantamessa of Red Dead Redemption) that understands The Divide&#x27;s core thesis: put two people in a box with dwindling resources and watch trust evaporate. Surfaced repeatedly in TikTok bunker movie recommendation compilations.</p><blockquote class=\"mt-6 pl-4 border-l-2 border-accent\"><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-secondary leading-relaxed italic\">“<!-- -->Hounsou and Reedus sell the claustrophobia completely. The moral weight of who deserves the last breath of air is genuinely agonizing.<!-- -->”</p></blockquote><blockquote class=\"mt-3 pl-4 border-l-2 border-separator\"><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-secondary leading-relaxed italic\">“<!-- -->An intriguing premise squandered by sluggish pacing and a script that never finds the tension its concept demands.<!-- -->”</p></blockquote><div class=\"mt-4\"><p class=\"text-[12px] font-semibold text-text-secondary uppercase tracking-wider mb-2\">Where to watch</p><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-primary\"><span class=\"text-accent font-medium\">Free: </span>Plex</p><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-primary mt-1\"><span class=\"text-text-secondary\">Rent/Buy: </span>Apple TV, Amazon Video</p></div><div class=\"mt-5 flex items-center gap-4\"><button class=\"flex items-center gap-1.5 py-1 transition-opacity hover:opacity-70\" aria-label=\"Save\"><svg width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#6E6E73\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\"><path d=\"M5 4a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h10a2 2 0 0 1 2 2v18l-7-4-7 4V4z\"></path></svg><span class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary\">Save for later</span></button><button class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary hover:text-text-primary transition-colors py-1\">Already seen</button><button class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary hover:text-text-primary transition-colors py-1\">Not for me</button></div></div></div></div></article><article class=\"border-b border-separator transition-all duration-700 ease-out cursor-pointer opacity-0 translate-y-6  px-6 py-6\"><div class=\"flex gap-5\"><div class=\"shrink-0 rounded-sm overflow-hidden\" style=\"width:140px\"><div class=\"w-full flex items-center justify-center rounded-sm\" style=\"aspect-ratio:2 / 3;background:linear-gradient(160deg, hsl(60, 12%, 90%) 0%, hsl(90, 18%, 82%) 100%)\"><span class=\"text-text-secondary text-[15px] font-semibold text-center px-6 opacity-60\">Domain</span></div></div><div class=\"flex-1 min-w-0\"><h3 class=\"text-[22px] font-bold text-text-primary leading-tight\">Domain<span class=\"inline-flex gap-2 ml-2\"><span class=\"text-[11px] font-semibold text-accent bg-accent/10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full\">New</span></span></h3><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-secondary mt-1\">2016<!-- --> · <!-- -->5.6<!-- -->/10</p><p class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary mt-1\">Nathaniel Atcheson</p><p class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary mt-2 leading-relaxed line-clamp-3\">A deadly flu virus has decimated the planet. Survivors are housed in individual underground bunkers with 70 years of sup...</p></div></div><div class=\"overflow-hidden transition-all duration-500 ease-out\" style=\"max-height:0;opacity:0\"><div class=\"pt-4\"><p class=\"text-[16px] text-text-primary leading-[1.6]\">A deadly flu virus has decimated the planet. Survivors are housed in individual underground bunkers with 70 years of supplies, connected only through a video network called Domain where seven strangers interact virtually. When members start disappearing from their pods one by one, the remaining survivors must figure out who -- or what -- is picking them off. This is The Divide reimagined for the Zoom era: isolation that&#x27;s both physical and psychological, trust built through screens, and a slow reveal that nothing is what it seems. The late-act twist recontextualizes the entire survival premise. Premiered at Austin&#x27;s Other Worlds sci-fi festival and circulates in YouTube isolation horror recommendation videos.</p><blockquote class=\"mt-6 pl-4 border-l-2 border-accent\"><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-secondary leading-relaxed italic\">“<!-- -->A tense, brooding portrayal of the human condition under the most confined and controlled circumstances. Ideas that aren&#x27;t confined by its budget.<!-- -->”</p></blockquote><blockquote class=\"mt-3 pl-4 border-l-2 border-separator\"><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-secondary leading-relaxed italic\">“<!-- -->Introduces a twist that completely negates any interesting, thought-provoking elements present up to that point. A betrayal of its own premise.<!-- -->”</p></blockquote><div class=\"mt-4\"><p class=\"text-[12px] font-semibold text-text-secondary uppercase tracking-wider mb-2\">Where to watch</p><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-primary mt-1\"><span class=\"text-text-secondary\">Rent/Buy: </span>Apple TV, Amazon Video, Fandango At Home</p></div><div class=\"mt-5 flex items-center gap-4\"><button class=\"flex items-center gap-1.5 py-1 transition-opacity hover:opacity-70\" aria-label=\"Save\"><svg width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#6E6E73\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\"><path d=\"M5 4a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h10a2 2 0 0 1 2 2v18l-7-4-7 4V4z\"></path></svg><span class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary\">Save for later</span></button><button class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary hover:text-text-primary transition-colors py-1\">Already seen</button><button class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary hover:text-text-primary transition-colors py-1\">Not for me</button></div></div></div></article><article class=\"border-b border-separator transition-all duration-700 ease-out cursor-pointer opacity-0 translate-y-6 \"><div class=\"w-full flex items-center justify-center \" style=\"aspect-ratio:16 / 9;background:linear-gradient(160deg, hsl(14, 12%, 90%) 0%, hsl(44, 18%, 82%) 100%)\"><span class=\"text-text-secondary text-[15px] font-semibold text-center px-6 opacity-60\">Containment</span></div><div class=\"px-6 py-6\"><h3 class=\"text-[28px] font-bold text-text-primary leading-tight\">Containment<span class=\"inline-flex gap-2 ml-2\"><span class=\"text-[11px] font-semibold text-accent bg-accent/10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full\">New</span></span></h3><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-secondary mt-1\">2015<!-- --> · <!-- -->4.9<!-- -->/10</p><p class=\"text-[15px] text-text-secondary mt-2 leading-relaxed\">Mark wakes in his council flat to find every door and window sealed with industrial epoxy. No electricity, no water, no ...</p><div class=\"overflow-hidden transition-all duration-500 ease-out\" style=\"max-height:0;opacity:0\"><div class=\"pt-4\"><p class=\"text-[16px] text-text-primary leading-[1.6]\">Mark wakes in his council flat to find every door and window sealed with industrial epoxy. No electricity, no water, no phone signal -- just a voice on the intercom repeating &#x27;please remain calm, the situation is under control.&#x27; An airborne virus that kills within 24 hours is allegedly loose, and the building&#x27;s residents must decide whether to trust the hazmat-suited figures outside or break free. The apartment block becomes a vertical bunker where floor-by-floor alliances form and shatter. Like The Divide, the sealed environment forces strangers into impossible choices about who to trust and who to sacrifice. Gained post-COVID relevance and resurfaced in TikTok quarantine horror recommendation threads. Available free on multiple platforms.</p><blockquote class=\"mt-6 pl-4 border-l-2 border-accent\"><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-secondary leading-relaxed italic\">“<!-- -->A great and brutal little indie thriller. Anything about viruses and lockdowns looks so ominous now. The claustrophobic flats and panicky people are rather prescient.<!-- -->”</p></blockquote><blockquote class=\"mt-3 pl-4 border-l-2 border-separator\"><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-secondary leading-relaxed italic\">“<!-- -->A dull movie where the story is nothing special and the characters are paper-thin. The ending is abrupt and unsatisfying.<!-- -->”</p></blockquote><div class=\"mt-4\"><p class=\"text-[12px] font-semibold text-text-secondary uppercase tracking-wider mb-2\">Where to watch</p><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-primary\"><span class=\"text-accent font-medium\">Free: </span>Tubi, Plex, Roku Channel, Hoopla</p><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-primary mt-1\"><span class=\"text-text-secondary\">Streaming: </span>Netflix</p><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-primary mt-1\"><span class=\"text-text-secondary\">Rent/Buy: </span>Amazon Video, Apple TV</p></div><div class=\"mt-5 flex items-center gap-4\"><button class=\"flex items-center gap-1.5 py-1 transition-opacity hover:opacity-70\" aria-label=\"Save\"><svg width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#6E6E73\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\"><path d=\"M5 4a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h10a2 2 0 0 1 2 2v18l-7-4-7 4V4z\"></path></svg><span class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary\">Save for later</span></button><button class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary hover:text-text-primary transition-colors py-1\">Already seen</button><button class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary hover:text-text-primary transition-colors py-1\">Not for me</button></div></div></div></div></article><article class=\"border-b border-separator transition-all duration-700 ease-out cursor-pointer opacity-0 translate-y-6  px-6 py-8\"><h3 class=\"text-[28px] font-bold text-text-primary leading-tight\">400 Days<span class=\"inline-flex gap-2 ml-2\"><span class=\"text-[11px] font-semibold text-accent bg-accent/10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full\">New</span></span></h3><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-secondary mt-1\">2015<!-- --> · <!-- -->4.4<!-- -->/10</p><p class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary mt-1\">Matt Osterman</p><p class=\"text-[15px] text-text-secondary mt-3 leading-relaxed\">Four astronauts (Brandon Routh, Caity Lotz, Ben Feldman, Dane Cook) undergo a 400-day isolation experiment in an undergr...</p><div class=\"overflow-hidden transition-all duration-500 ease-out\" style=\"max-height:0;opacity:0\"><div class=\"pt-4\"><p class=\"text-[16px] text-text-primary leading-[1.6]\">Four astronauts (Brandon Routh, Caity Lotz, Ben Feldman, Dane Cook) undergo a 400-day isolation experiment in an underground bunker simulating deep-space travel conditions. As paranoia mounts and hallucinations intensify, a malfunction forces them to exit early -- but the world outside has changed in ways that blur the line between simulation and reality. Inspired by the real MARS-500 experiment, the film takes The Divide&#x27;s bunker premise and adds epistemological horror: you can&#x27;t trust the environment, the other people, or your own perceptions. The confined underground setting and deteriorating group dynamics are textbook Divide DNA. Circulates in YouTube sci-fi deep-cut compilations and TikTok bunker movie recommendation lists.</p><blockquote class=\"mt-6 pl-4 border-l-2 border-accent\"><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-secondary leading-relaxed italic\">“<!-- -->Stylish and atmospheric with a genuinely intriguing concept. The ambiguous ending rewards viewers who enjoy puzzles over answers.<!-- -->”</p></blockquote><blockquote class=\"mt-3 pl-4 border-l-2 border-separator\"><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-secondary leading-relaxed italic\">“<!-- -->A structural mess that fumbles its premise with a preposterous second half. All setup, no payoff.<!-- -->”</p></blockquote><div class=\"mt-4\"><p class=\"text-[12px] font-semibold text-text-secondary uppercase tracking-wider mb-2\">Where to watch</p><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-primary\"><span class=\"text-accent font-medium\">Free: </span>Pluto TV, Roku Channel, Kanopy, Plex</p><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-primary mt-1\"><span class=\"text-text-secondary\">Rent/Buy: </span>Apple TV, Amazon Video, Fandango At Home</p></div><div class=\"mt-5 flex items-center gap-4\"><button class=\"flex items-center gap-1.5 py-1 transition-opacity hover:opacity-70\" aria-label=\"Save\"><svg width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#6E6E73\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\"><path d=\"M5 4a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h10a2 2 0 0 1 2 2v18l-7-4-7 4V4z\"></path></svg><span class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary\">Save for later</span></button><button class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary hover:text-text-primary transition-colors py-1\">Already seen</button><button class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary hover:text-text-primary transition-colors py-1\">Not for me</button></div></div></div></article><section class=\"py-16 px-6\"><div class=\"max-w-2xl mx-auto text-center transition-all duration-700 ease-out opacity-0 translate-y-4\"><div class=\"relative inline-block\"><svg class=\"absolute -left-8 top-1/2 -translate-y-1/2\" width=\"20\" height=\"48\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 48\" fill=\"none\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\"><path d=\"M16 4C8 6 5 14 4 24C5 34 8 42 16 44\" stroke=\"#0496FF\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" fill=\"none\"></path></svg><svg class=\"absolute -right-8 top-1/2 -translate-y-1/2\" width=\"20\" height=\"48\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 48\" fill=\"none\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\"><path d=\"M4 4C12 6 15 14 16 24C15 34 12 42 4 44\" stroke=\"#0496FF\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" fill=\"none\"></path></svg><h3 class=\"text-[28px] font-bold text-text-primary px-4\">Sealed in</h3></div><p class=\"text-[14px] font-normal text-text-secondary mt-3\">Bunkers, shelters, and nowhere to go</p></div></section><article class=\"border-b border-separator transition-all duration-700 ease-out cursor-pointer opacity-0 translate-y-6 \"><div class=\"w-full flex items-center justify-center \" style=\"aspect-ratio:2 / 3;background:linear-gradient(160deg, hsl(73, 12%, 90%) 0%, hsl(103, 18%, 82%) 100%)\"><span class=\"text-text-secondary text-[15px] font-semibold text-center px-6 opacity-60\">Dead Within</span></div><div class=\"px-6 py-6\"><h3 class=\"text-[28px] font-bold text-text-primary leading-tight\">Dead Within<span class=\"inline-flex gap-2 ml-2\"><span class=\"text-[11px] font-semibold text-accent bg-accent/10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full\">New</span></span></h3><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-secondary mt-1\">2014<!-- --> · <!-- -->3.8<!-- -->/10</p><p class=\"text-[15px] text-text-secondary mt-2 leading-relaxed\">Six months after a deadly outbreak, Mike and Kim survive by isolating themselves in a cabin with one absolute rule: neve...</p><div class=\"overflow-hidden transition-all duration-500 ease-out\" style=\"max-height:0;opacity:0\"><div class=\"pt-4\"><p class=\"text-[16px] text-text-primary leading-[1.6]\">Six months after a deadly outbreak, Mike and Kim survive by isolating themselves in a cabin with one absolute rule: never open the door. Mike leaves periodically for supplies; Kim stays behind, alone with her deteriorating sanity. Flashbacks reveal they once shared the cabin with another couple and a baby -- all lost to tainted food. This is The Divide&#x27;s psychological disintegration concentrated into a two-person dynamic. There are no zombies on screen -- the horror is entirely internal, watching a woman&#x27;s mind fracture under the weight of isolation, grief, and paranoia. Amy Cale Peterson delivers a raw, committed performance as someone who may be losing her grip or may be the only one seeing clearly. The film asks The Divide&#x27;s central question: what&#x27;s more dangerous, the threat outside or the people you&#x27;re sealed in with?</p><blockquote class=\"mt-6 pl-4 border-l-2 border-accent\"><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-secondary leading-relaxed italic\">“<!-- -->An atypical zombie movie where the emphasis is on psychological disintegration rather than creature attacks. Peterson&#x27;s performance is a slow-burn masterclass in unraveling.<!-- -->”</p></blockquote><blockquote class=\"mt-3 pl-4 border-l-2 border-separator\"><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-secondary leading-relaxed italic\">“<!-- -->Total lack of tension, deadly dull storyline, and cheaply produced. A zombie movie with no zombies and no scares.<!-- -->”</p></blockquote><div class=\"mt-4\"><p class=\"text-[12px] font-semibold text-text-secondary uppercase tracking-wider mb-2\">Where to watch</p><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-primary\"><span class=\"text-accent font-medium\">Free: </span>Tubi, Plex, Roku Channel</p><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-primary mt-1\"><span class=\"text-text-secondary\">Rent/Buy: </span>Amazon Video</p></div><div class=\"mt-5 flex items-center gap-4\"><button class=\"flex items-center gap-1.5 py-1 transition-opacity hover:opacity-70\" aria-label=\"Save\"><svg width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#6E6E73\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\"><path d=\"M5 4a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h10a2 2 0 0 1 2 2v18l-7-4-7 4V4z\"></path></svg><span class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary\">Save for later</span></button><button class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary hover:text-text-primary transition-colors py-1\">Already seen</button><button class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary hover:text-text-primary transition-colors py-1\">Not for me</button></div></div></div></div></article><article class=\"border-b border-separator transition-all duration-700 ease-out cursor-pointer opacity-0 translate-y-6  px-6 py-6\"><div class=\"flex gap-5\"><div class=\"shrink-0 rounded-sm overflow-hidden\" style=\"width:140px\"><div class=\"w-full flex items-center justify-center rounded-sm\" style=\"aspect-ratio:2 / 3;background:linear-gradient(160deg, hsl(215, 12%, 90%) 0%, hsl(245, 18%, 82%) 100%)\"><span class=\"text-text-secondary text-[15px] font-semibold text-center px-6 opacity-60\">Extinction</span></div></div><div class=\"flex-1 min-w-0\"><h3 class=\"text-[22px] font-bold text-text-primary leading-tight\">Extinction<span class=\"inline-flex gap-2 ml-2\"><span class=\"text-[11px] font-semibold text-accent bg-accent/10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full\">New</span></span></h3><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-secondary mt-1\">2015<!-- --> · <!-- -->5.8<!-- -->/10</p><p class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary mt-1\">Miguel Angel Vivas</p><p class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary mt-2 leading-relaxed line-clamp-3\">Nine years after a zombie plague, Patrick (Matthew Fox) and Jack (Jeffrey Donovan) survive in the snowbound ghost town o...</p></div></div><div class=\"overflow-hidden transition-all duration-500 ease-out\" style=\"max-height:0;opacity:0\"><div class=\"pt-4\"><p class=\"text-[16px] text-text-primary leading-[1.6]\">Nine years after a zombie plague, Patrick (Matthew Fox) and Jack (Jeffrey Donovan) survive in the snowbound ghost town of Harmony with Jack&#x27;s young daughter. The two men haven&#x27;t spoken in years despite living next door -- a festering grudge has turned neighbors into enemies. When Patrick discovers the infected have evolved into something far more dangerous, the men must overcome their hatred to protect the girl. This is The Divide&#x27;s interpersonal hostility transplanted to a frozen wasteland: two people sealed in proximity by circumstance, their relationship poisoned by power dynamics and resentment, forced to cooperate when the external threat escalates. The snow-covered isolation and character-driven approach set it apart from typical zombie fare. Frequently appears in YouTube &#x27;underrated zombie movies&#x27; and TikTok survival horror recommendation lists.</p><blockquote class=\"mt-6 pl-4 border-l-2 border-accent\"><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-secondary leading-relaxed italic\">“<!-- -->Far from a masterpiece but takes its characters seriously and doesn&#x27;t condescend to the audience. A solid zombie survival flick with genuine emotional stakes.<!-- -->”</p></blockquote><blockquote class=\"mt-3 pl-4 border-l-2 border-separator\"><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-secondary leading-relaxed italic\">“<!-- -->I was in for zombie horror but only got that in the last twenty minutes. Before that, it&#x27;s a boring family drama with too little action and bad camera work.<!-- -->”</p></blockquote><div class=\"mt-4\"><p class=\"text-[12px] font-semibold text-text-secondary uppercase tracking-wider mb-2\">Where to watch</p><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-primary\"><span class=\"text-accent font-medium\">Free: </span>Plex</p><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-primary mt-1\"><span class=\"text-text-secondary\">Streaming: </span>Philo, fuboTV</p><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-primary mt-1\"><span class=\"text-text-secondary\">Rent/Buy: </span>Apple TV, Amazon Video</p></div><div class=\"mt-5 flex items-center gap-4\"><button class=\"flex items-center gap-1.5 py-1 transition-opacity hover:opacity-70\" aria-label=\"Save\"><svg width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#6E6E73\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\"><path d=\"M5 4a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h10a2 2 0 0 1 2 2v18l-7-4-7 4V4z\"></path></svg><span class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary\">Save for later</span></button><button class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary hover:text-text-primary transition-colors py-1\">Already seen</button><button class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary hover:text-text-primary transition-colors py-1\">Not for me</button></div></div></div></article><article class=\"border-b border-separator transition-all duration-700 ease-out cursor-pointer opacity-0 translate-y-6 \"><div class=\"w-full flex items-center justify-center \" style=\"aspect-ratio:16 / 9;background:linear-gradient(160deg, hsl(215, 12%, 90%) 0%, hsl(245, 18%, 82%) 100%)\"><span class=\"text-text-secondary text-[15px] font-semibold text-center px-6 opacity-60\">Level 16</span></div><div class=\"px-6 py-6\"><h3 class=\"text-[28px] font-bold text-text-primary leading-tight\">Level 16<span class=\"inline-flex gap-2 ml-2\"><span class=\"text-[11px] font-semibold text-accent bg-accent/10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full\">New</span></span></h3><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-secondary mt-1\">2018<!-- --> · <!-- -->6.1<!-- -->/10</p><p class=\"text-[15px] text-text-secondary mt-2 leading-relaxed\">At Vestalis Academy, teenage girls are raised in a sterile, windowless facility and drilled in the &#x27;feminine virtues&#x27; --...</p><div class=\"overflow-hidden transition-all duration-500 ease-out\" style=\"max-height:0;opacity:0\"><div class=\"pt-4\"><p class=\"text-[16px] text-text-primary leading-[1.6]\">At Vestalis Academy, teenage girls are raised in a sterile, windowless facility and drilled in the &#x27;feminine virtues&#x27; -- obedience, cleanliness, humility, patience. They believe they&#x27;re being prepared for adoption. The truth is far worse: the Academy is a rejuvenation clinic where girls are raised in UV-free environments so their unblemished skin can be harvested for wealthy buyers. When two girls on Level 16 discover the truth, they must navigate the facility&#x27;s power structure to escape. Like The Divide, the horror is institutional: a confined space where authority figures control every aspect of survival, and the captives must decide whether to comply or resist. The sterile corridors are their bunker, the headmistress their warden. Rotten Tomatoes certified at 83%. Circulates heavily in Film Twitter threads about feminist horror and dystopian deep cuts.</p><blockquote class=\"mt-6 pl-4 border-l-2 border-accent\"><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-secondary leading-relaxed italic\">“<!-- -->Timely, challenging, full of great acting and an engaging story. Should not be missed by fans of 1984 or The Handmaid&#x27;s Tale.<!-- -->”</p></blockquote><blockquote class=\"mt-3 pl-4 border-l-2 border-separator\"><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-secondary leading-relaxed italic\">“<!-- -->For most viewers this will come in at a level below an average Twilight Zone episode. The premise promises more than the execution delivers.<!-- -->”</p></blockquote><div class=\"mt-4\"><p class=\"text-[12px] font-semibold text-text-secondary uppercase tracking-wider mb-2\">Where to watch</p><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-primary\"><span class=\"text-accent font-medium\">Free: </span>Pluto TV</p><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-primary mt-1\"><span class=\"text-text-secondary\">Rent/Buy: </span>Apple TV, Amazon Video, Google Play</p></div><div class=\"mt-5 flex items-center gap-4\"><button class=\"flex items-center gap-1.5 py-1 transition-opacity hover:opacity-70\" aria-label=\"Save\"><svg width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#6E6E73\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\"><path d=\"M5 4a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h10a2 2 0 0 1 2 2v18l-7-4-7 4V4z\"></path></svg><span class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary\">Save for later</span></button><button class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary hover:text-text-primary transition-colors py-1\">Already seen</button><button class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary hover:text-text-primary transition-colors py-1\">Not for me</button></div></div></div></div></article><article class=\"border-b border-separator transition-all duration-700 ease-out cursor-pointer opacity-0 translate-y-6  px-6 py-8\"><h3 class=\"text-[28px] font-bold text-text-primary leading-tight\">3022<span class=\"inline-flex gap-2 ml-2\"><span class=\"text-[11px] font-semibold text-accent bg-accent/10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full\">New</span></span></h3><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-secondary mt-1\">2019<!-- --> · <!-- -->4.5<!-- -->/10</p><p class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary mt-1\">John Suits</p><p class=\"text-[15px] text-text-secondary mt-3 leading-relaxed\">In 2190, a crew of four astronauts (Omar Epps, Kate Walsh, Angus Macfadyen) aboard a deep-space station witness Earth&#x27;s ...</p><div class=\"overflow-hidden transition-all duration-500 ease-out\" style=\"max-height:0;opacity:0\"><div class=\"pt-4\"><p class=\"text-[16px] text-text-primary leading-[1.6]\">In 2190, a crew of four astronauts (Omar Epps, Kate Walsh, Angus Macfadyen) aboard a deep-space station witness Earth&#x27;s destruction from millions of miles away. With no planet to return to and a dying station around them, they must decide whether survival has any meaning. The grief, rage, and blame that follow mirror The Divide&#x27;s emotional arc: people sealed in a metal box, stripped of purpose, turning on each other as hope evaporates. The station becomes their bunker, the void of space their nuclear wasteland. Epps and Walsh deliver committed performances that elevate the claustrophobic premise. Found its audience on Netflix and circulates in YouTube space isolation recommendation compilations and TikTok &#x27;movies that will destroy you&#x27; lists.</p><blockquote class=\"mt-6 pl-4 border-l-2 border-accent\"><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-secondary leading-relaxed italic\">“<!-- -->Delivers enough tense atmospherics to reward sci-fi fans willing to sit with existential dread. Epps handles the stalwart hero thing well, Walsh is effectively intense.<!-- -->”</p></blockquote><blockquote class=\"mt-3 pl-4 border-l-2 border-separator\"><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-secondary leading-relaxed italic\">“<!-- -->Mundane, generic, and downright boring with way too little of interest going on. A space movie where nothing happens in space.<!-- -->”</p></blockquote><div class=\"mt-4\"><p class=\"text-[12px] font-semibold text-text-secondary uppercase tracking-wider mb-2\">Where to watch</p><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-primary\"><span class=\"text-accent font-medium\">Free: </span>Plex</p><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-primary mt-1\"><span class=\"text-text-secondary\">Streaming: </span>Netflix</p><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-primary mt-1\"><span class=\"text-text-secondary\">Rent/Buy: </span>Apple TV, Amazon Video</p></div><div class=\"mt-5 flex items-center gap-4\"><button class=\"flex items-center gap-1.5 py-1 transition-opacity hover:opacity-70\" aria-label=\"Save\"><svg width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#6E6E73\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\"><path d=\"M5 4a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h10a2 2 0 0 1 2 2v18l-7-4-7 4V4z\"></path></svg><span class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary\">Save for later</span></button><button class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary hover:text-text-primary transition-colors py-1\">Already seen</button><button class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary hover:text-text-primary transition-colors py-1\">Not for me</button></div></div></div></article><article class=\"border-b border-separator transition-all duration-700 ease-out cursor-pointer opacity-0 translate-y-6 \"><div class=\"w-full flex items-center justify-center \" style=\"aspect-ratio:2 / 3;background:linear-gradient(160deg, hsl(299, 12%, 90%) 0%, hsl(329, 18%, 82%) 100%)\"><span class=\"text-text-secondary text-[15px] font-semibold text-center px-6 opacity-60\">Last Survivors</span></div><div class=\"px-6 py-6\"><h3 class=\"text-[28px] font-bold text-text-primary leading-tight\">Last Survivors<span class=\"inline-flex gap-2 ml-2\"><span class=\"text-[11px] font-semibold text-accent bg-accent/10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full\">New</span></span></h3><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-secondary mt-1\">2021<!-- --> · <!-- -->5<!-- -->/10</p><p class=\"text-[15px] text-text-secondary mt-2 leading-relaxed\">Twenty years after a devastating world war, Troy (Stephen Moyer) and his adult son Jake (Drew Van Acker) survive in tota...</p><div class=\"overflow-hidden transition-all duration-500 ease-out\" style=\"max-height:0;opacity:0\"><div class=\"pt-4\"><p class=\"text-[16px] text-text-primary leading-[1.6]\">Twenty years after a devastating world war, Troy (Stephen Moyer) and his adult son Jake (Drew Van Acker) survive in total isolation in the wilderness. Troy has raised Jake with one absolute rule: any outsider is a lethal threat to be eliminated on sight. When Troy is injured and Jake ventures out for medicine, he encounters Henrietta (Alicia Silverstone) and begins questioning everything his father taught him. This is The Divide&#x27;s power dynamics in a father-son crucible: one person&#x27;s paranoid control over another, justified by survival but rooted in something darker. The film deliberately deconstructs the survivalist fantasy, asking whether the bunker mentality itself becomes the greatest threat. Premiered at FrightFest and gained traction on Tubi, where it surfaces in post-apocalyptic recommendation algorithms.</p><blockquote class=\"mt-6 pl-4 border-l-2 border-accent\"><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-secondary leading-relaxed italic\">“<!-- -->Both an edge-of-your-seat thriller and a fascinating character study. Alicia Silverstone&#x27;s mature performance is the best thing about the movie.<!-- -->”</p></blockquote><blockquote class=\"mt-3 pl-4 border-l-2 border-separator\"><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-secondary leading-relaxed italic\">“<!-- -->The story doesn&#x27;t develop organically -- logical gaps and narrative lurches are hard to ignore. The dialogues feel unnatural throughout.<!-- -->”</p></blockquote><div class=\"mt-4\"><p class=\"text-[12px] font-semibold text-text-secondary uppercase tracking-wider mb-2\">Where to watch</p><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-primary\"><span class=\"text-accent font-medium\">Free: </span>Tubi, Plex</p><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-primary mt-1\"><span class=\"text-text-secondary\">Rent/Buy: </span>Apple TV, Amazon Video, Fandango At Home</p></div><div class=\"mt-5 flex items-center gap-4\"><button class=\"flex items-center gap-1.5 py-1 transition-opacity hover:opacity-70\" aria-label=\"Save\"><svg width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#6E6E73\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\"><path d=\"M5 4a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h10a2 2 0 0 1 2 2v18l-7-4-7 4V4z\"></path></svg><span class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary\">Save for later</span></button><button class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary hover:text-text-primary transition-colors py-1\">Already seen</button><button class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary hover:text-text-primary transition-colors py-1\">Not for me</button></div></div></div></div></article><section class=\"py-16 px-6\"><div class=\"max-w-2xl mx-auto text-center transition-all duration-700 ease-out opacity-0 translate-y-4\"><div class=\"relative inline-block\"><svg class=\"absolute -left-8 top-1/2 -translate-y-1/2\" width=\"20\" height=\"48\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 48\" fill=\"none\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\"><path d=\"M16 4C8 6 5 14 4 24C5 34 8 42 16 44\" stroke=\"#0496FF\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" fill=\"none\"></path></svg><svg class=\"absolute -right-8 top-1/2 -translate-y-1/2\" width=\"20\" height=\"48\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 48\" fill=\"none\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\"><path d=\"M4 4C12 6 15 14 16 24C15 34 12 42 4 44\" stroke=\"#0496FF\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" fill=\"none\"></path></svg><h3 class=\"text-[28px] font-bold text-text-primary px-4\">Sealed in</h3></div><p class=\"text-[14px] font-normal text-text-secondary mt-3\">Bunkers, shelters, and nowhere to go</p></div></section><article class=\"border-b border-separator transition-all duration-700 ease-out cursor-pointer opacity-0 translate-y-6  px-6 py-6\"><div class=\"flex gap-5\"><div class=\"shrink-0 rounded-sm overflow-hidden\" style=\"width:140px\"><div class=\"w-full flex items-center justify-center rounded-sm\" style=\"aspect-ratio:2 / 3;background:linear-gradient(160deg, hsl(245, 12%, 90%) 0%, hsl(275, 18%, 82%) 100%)\"><span class=\"text-text-secondary text-[15px] font-semibold text-center px-6 opacity-60\">Shelter</span></div></div><div class=\"flex-1 min-w-0\"><h3 class=\"text-[22px] font-bold text-text-primary leading-tight\">Shelter<span class=\"inline-flex gap-2 ml-2\"><span class=\"text-[11px] font-semibold text-accent bg-accent/10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full\">New</span></span></h3><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-secondary mt-1\">2015<!-- --> · <!-- -->4.8<!-- -->/10</p><p class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary mt-1\">Wrion Bowling, Adam C. Caudill</p><p class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary mt-2 leading-relaxed line-clamp-3\">Five coworkers from the same office building are sealed in its basement bomb shelter when a nuclear strike hits the city...</p></div></div><div class=\"overflow-hidden transition-all duration-500 ease-out\" style=\"max-height:0;opacity:0\"><div class=\"pt-4\"><p class=\"text-[16px] text-text-primary leading-[1.6]\">Five coworkers from the same office building are sealed in its basement bomb shelter when a nuclear strike hits the city above. With enough supplies to outlast the fallout, the group settles in -- but weeks stretch into months, and one room proves catastrophically small for five people. Time begins losing meaning, alliances calcify and crack, and the psychological toll of indefinite confinement pushes each person toward their breaking point. This is the most direct Divide analog in the batch: same nuclear scenario, same bunker, same group disintegration arc. The intentionally disorienting time skips mirror the survivors&#x27; own fractured sense of reality. A true deep cut that surfaces only in hardcore bunker movie IMDB lists and niche YouTube compilations.</p><blockquote class=\"mt-6 pl-4 border-l-2 border-accent\"><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-secondary leading-relaxed italic\">“<!-- -->People don&#x27;t get this movie. They&#x27;re locked in a bunker losing their minds -- time is slowly losing meaning, and that&#x27;s the point. The disorientation is the horror.<!-- -->”</p></blockquote><blockquote class=\"mt-3 pl-4 border-l-2 border-separator\"><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-secondary leading-relaxed italic\">“<!-- -->Way too long with pacing that should have been much tighter. A decent concept that needed a better script and a stronger editor.<!-- -->”</p></blockquote><div class=\"mt-4\"><p class=\"text-[12px] font-semibold text-text-secondary uppercase tracking-wider mb-2\">Where to watch</p><p class=\"text-[14px] text-text-primary mt-1\"><span class=\"text-text-secondary\">Rent/Buy: </span>Apple TV, Amazon Video, Fandango At Home</p></div><div class=\"mt-5 flex items-center gap-4\"><button class=\"flex items-center gap-1.5 py-1 transition-opacity hover:opacity-70\" aria-label=\"Save\"><svg width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#6E6E73\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\"><path d=\"M5 4a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h10a2 2 0 0 1 2 2v18l-7-4-7 4V4z\"></path></svg><span class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary\">Save for later</span></button><button class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary hover:text-text-primary transition-colors py-1\">Already seen</button><button class=\"text-[13px] text-text-secondary hover:text-text-primary transition-colors py-1\">Not for me</button></div></div></div></article></div></section><footer class=\"pt-24 pb-16 px-6 bg-surface\"><div class=\"max-w-2xl mx-auto text-center transition-all duration-700 ease-out opacity-0 translate-y-4\"><div class=\"flex justify-center mb-8 opacity-40\"><svg width=\"64\" height=\"16\" viewBox=\"0 0 64 16\" fill=\"none\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\"><path d=\"M2 8C8 3 14 13 20 8C26 3 32 13 38 8C44 3 50 13 56 8C60 5 62 6 62 8\" stroke=\"#0496FF\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" fill=\"none\"></path></svg></div><p class=\"text-[14px] font-normal text-text-secondary\">A film list, not an algorithm</p><p class=\